docs.lead_paragraph: 9 P.M. (History) THE CRUMBLING OF AMERICA The Romans had their roads and aqueducts; the Mayans, their pyramids and palaces. But what happens when a great civilization neglects its infrastructure? This two-hour report investigates the deterioration of highways, tunnels, dams, levees, ports and pipelines in the United States, including more than 70,000 bridges rated as structurally deficient and 25,000 miles of commercial waterways and locks that have exceeded their 50-year design life. One warning: the 2007 collapse of the Interstate 35W Bridge, above, in Minneapolis. One segment looks at structures on a ''worst of'' list. Another introduces technologies and detection techniques to prevent catastrophes. 7 A.M. (CBS) THE EARLY SHOW Reba Toney talks about her book, ''The Rating Game: The Foolproof Formula for Finding Your Perfect Soul Mate''; also, the recession's effect on pets.
